1
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:41,180
=In Marriage and Beyond=

2
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:44,180
=Episode 7=

3
00:01:45,110 --> 00:01:45,950
But

4
00:01:46,110 --> 00:01:47,830
that woman is quite pitiful,

5
00:01:48,320 --> 00:01:50,470
for she completely depends on my boyfriend
for her livelihood.

6
00:01:52,830 --> 00:01:54,240
Can you still find such people these days?

7
00:01:54,630 --> 00:01:55,720
She acts so proud,

8
00:01:56,270 --> 00:01:57,990
but deep down she knows that

9
00:01:58,080 --> 00:01:58,990
without my boyfriend,

10
00:01:58,990 --> 00:02:00,350
she'd be nothing,

11
00:02:00,350 --> 00:02:01,550
have nothing.

12
00:02:01,720 --> 00:02:02,680
You know,

13
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:04,410
how could she dare to leave?

14
00:02:06,690 --> 00:02:07,650
It's simple.

15
00:02:09,220 --> 00:02:10,750
As long as you two get married,

16
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:12,440
she'll give up.

17
00:02:12,630 --> 00:02:13,600
It's not like

18
00:02:14,750 --> 00:02:16,040
she'd go become the other woman.

19
00:02:20,160 --> 00:02:21,350
In this day and age,

20
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:23,840
being the other woman is very costly.

21
00:02:24,510 --> 00:02:26,230
Once it's out on the internet,

22
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:28,120
oh my god, her reputation is ruined,

23
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:29,560
and it'll be hard for her to find a job.

24
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:32,120
So it's better if you get married soon.

25
00:02:33,240 --> 00:02:35,190
Marriage is just a certificate,

26
00:02:35,860 --> 00:02:37,630
I'm not that concerned about it.

27
00:02:38,450 --> 00:02:41,190
After all, my boyfriend can't live without me.

28
00:02:45,050 --> 00:02:45,890
That's good.

29
00:02:47,180 --> 00:02:48,900
Actually, my boyfriend likes me

30
00:02:50,020 --> 00:02:51,620
not just because

31
00:02:51,620 --> 00:02:53,860
we support each other at work.

32
00:02:54,380 --> 00:02:56,980
It's more because we connect.

33
00:02:59,940 --> 00:03:00,940
That woman,

34
00:03:02,060 --> 00:03:05,420
she just has a fling with my boyfriend,

35
00:03:06,140 --> 00:03:07,660
but she doesn't understand

36
00:03:07,860 --> 00:03:10,020
or feel the pain he's going through.

37
00:03:11,540 --> 00:03:13,940
So every time my boyfriend's at his lowest,

38
00:03:14,540 --> 00:03:16,340
he always comes to find me first.

39
00:03:17,580 --> 00:03:18,620
I think

40
00:03:19,180 --> 00:03:21,420
we're true soulmates.

41
00:03:27,050 --> 00:03:28,580
Ms. Ning, do you know?

42
00:03:28,780 --> 00:03:30,580
My last birthday with my boyfriend

43
00:03:30,580 --> 00:03:31,740
- (Honey, I've arrived.)
- was so romantic.

44
00:03:31,740 --> 00:03:32,820
He gave

45
00:03:32,820 --> 00:03:34,300
me a unique gift.

46
00:03:36,260 --> 00:03:37,100
Wait.

47
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:38,140
Waiter,

48
00:03:38,480 --> 00:03:39,710
we want

49
00:03:39,820 --> 00:03:41,350
one more set of tableware, thank you.

50
00:03:42,580 --> 00:03:44,060
Isn't Director Qin not coming?

51
00:03:44,380 --> 00:03:45,420
It's not him.

52
00:03:49,380 --> 00:03:50,220
Honey,

53
00:03:50,300 --> 00:03:51,140
over here.

54
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:52,340
Honey.

55
00:03:56,620 --> 00:03:57,460
Sit.

56
00:04:02,220 --> 00:04:03,060
Manager Tian.

57
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:06,590
Mr. Hu.

58
00:04:07,760 --> 00:04:08,600
Honey,

59
00:04:09,260 --> 00:04:11,940
is Manager Tian is in charge of
your new project?

60
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:14,340
Manager Tian takes good care of me

61
00:04:14,340 --> 00:04:15,380
and even treated me to a meal.

62
00:04:15,540 --> 00:04:16,860
You're paying the check.

63
00:04:17,060 --> 00:04:17,900
Honey,

64
00:04:19,660 --> 00:04:20,740
it's surely on me.

65
00:04:28,980 --> 00:04:30,340
What were you two talking about?

66
00:04:30,620 --> 00:04:31,780
About her boyfriend.

67
00:04:36,740 --> 00:04:37,660
Manager Tian said

68
00:04:38,740 --> 00:04:39,980
her boyfriend

69
00:04:39,980 --> 00:04:41,380
is an entrepreneur like you.

70
00:04:44,420 --> 00:04:45,660
Not as good as Mr. Hu.

71
00:04:46,540 --> 00:04:48,380
And Manager Tian is quite impressive.

72
00:04:48,860 --> 00:04:49,700
She said

73
00:04:50,340 --> 00:04:51,180
whether it's love

74
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:52,340
or work,

75
00:04:52,980 --> 00:04:54,020
she keeps her boyfriend

76
00:04:54,300 --> 00:04:55,660
wrapped around her finger.

77
00:04:56,180 --> 00:04:57,180
So...

78
00:04:57,780 --> 00:04:59,540
her boyfriend can't live without her.

79
00:05:01,980 --> 00:05:02,940
For real?

80
00:05:02,980 --> 00:05:03,860
Yes.

81
00:05:06,260 --> 00:05:07,180
Manger Tian,

82
00:05:08,580 --> 00:05:09,860
you're very good to your boyfriend,

83
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:11,660
so he…

84
00:05:11,980 --> 00:05:13,340
must be very happy, right?

85
00:05:18,700 --> 00:05:20,620
Not as happy as you and Ms. Ning.

86
00:05:21,660 --> 00:05:23,180
You two are the perfect match,

87
00:05:23,940 --> 00:05:24,980
respectful and loving,

88
00:05:25,940 --> 00:05:26,940
making people envious.

89
00:05:28,580 --> 00:05:30,540
Manager Tian also told me

90
00:05:30,940 --> 00:05:32,580
her boyfriend is really romantic

91
00:05:32,860 --> 00:05:34,160
and gave her

92
00:05:34,540 --> 00:05:36,000
a unique gift.

93
00:05:38,380 --> 00:05:40,340
Honey, doesn't that sound just like you?

94
00:05:41,940 --> 00:05:42,820
A few days ago,

95
00:05:43,060 --> 00:05:44,060
my husband

96
00:05:44,060 --> 00:05:45,460
also gave me a gift.

97
00:05:47,060 --> 00:05:48,460
A hotel membership card.

98
00:05:53,780 --> 00:05:55,020
The password is your birthday.

99
00:05:55,420 --> 00:05:56,580
I really love this place.

100
00:05:56,880 --> 00:05:58,300
I hope we can

101
00:05:58,300 --> 00:05:59,860
create our memories here.

102
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:02,460
I hope when you come back here next time,

103
00:06:02,860 --> 00:06:03,820
you'll only

104
00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:05,220
think of me.

105
00:06:09,380 --> 00:06:10,340
This card

106
00:06:10,420 --> 00:06:11,940
is very special to me,

107
00:06:12,620 --> 00:06:13,740
because this hotel

108
00:06:14,420 --> 00:06:16,340
means a lot to us.

109
00:06:21,670 --> 00:06:22,900
Mr. Hu, you're really romantic.

110
00:06:24,460 --> 00:06:25,860
What's so romantic about him?

111
00:06:25,860 --> 00:06:27,260
He doesn't understand romance.

112
00:06:27,260 --> 00:06:28,540
But there's no perfect person

113
00:06:28,540 --> 00:06:30,100
in this world, right?

114
00:06:30,860 --> 00:06:32,220
As long as we love each other,

115
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:33,380
and we can tolerate

116
00:06:33,460 --> 00:06:34,940
and understand each other's flaws,

117
00:06:35,540 --> 00:06:36,580
we can overcome

118
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:39,100
any problems.

119
00:06:39,940 --> 00:06:40,900
After all,

120
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:43,420
we're one, aren't we?

121
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:51,420
She also said that

122
00:06:51,420 --> 00:06:52,700
she and her boyfriend

123
00:06:53,060 --> 00:06:55,180
are soulmates,

124
00:06:55,340 --> 00:06:56,660
truly in sync.

125
00:06:56,780 --> 00:06:58,780
I've always wanted to ask you, honey,

126
00:06:59,220 --> 00:07:00,180
what about us?

127
00:07:01,260 --> 00:07:02,180
Are we soulmates?

128
00:07:07,140 --> 00:07:07,980
Us?

129
00:07:08,580 --> 00:07:09,420
We…

130
00:07:10,140 --> 00:07:11,340
of course, we…

131
00:07:11,340 --> 00:07:12,180
Mr. Hu,

132
00:07:13,660 --> 00:07:14,500
Ms. Ning,

133
00:07:15,210 --> 00:07:16,060
it occurs to me

134
00:07:16,060 --> 00:07:17,620
that I have a case to be wrapped up.

135
00:07:19,220 --> 00:07:20,100
Excuse me.

136
00:07:39,260 --> 00:07:40,500
She has left.

137
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:41,420
What are you looking at?

138
00:07:45,060 --> 00:07:45,900
Honey,

139
00:07:47,140 --> 00:07:48,420
I think you've changed.

140
00:07:49,180 --> 00:07:50,500
You didn't used to

141
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:52,380
show off your love in public.

142
00:07:54,060 --> 00:07:55,580
She is right in front me.

143
00:07:57,260 --> 00:07:58,260
If I don't change,

144
00:08:01,140 --> 00:08:02,070
what am I waiting for?

145
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:08,540
Honey,

146
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:11,420
are you misunderstanding something?

147
00:08:13,260 --> 00:08:15,060
Was her boyfriend you?

148
00:08:16,980 --> 00:08:18,180
What are you talking about?

149
00:08:18,180 --> 00:08:19,020
That's nonsense.

150
00:08:19,020 --> 00:08:20,220
Absolute nonsense.

151
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:21,940
Then why did she react so strongly?

152
00:08:23,580 --> 00:08:24,860
Is that hotel membership card

153
00:08:24,860 --> 00:08:26,460
from you?

154
00:08:27,460 --> 00:08:28,500
Of course not.

155
00:08:32,340 --> 00:08:33,460
What did you...

156
00:08:34,420 --> 00:08:35,340
talk about just now?

157
00:08:35,340 --> 00:08:36,900
That's not your concern.

158
00:08:38,140 --> 00:08:39,380
I want to hear what you have to say.

159
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:43,300
Manager Tian and me,

160
00:08:43,900 --> 00:08:46,060
we're merely business partner.

161
00:08:53,740 --> 00:08:55,300
If…

162
00:08:56,380 --> 00:08:58,220
I said something wrong
at business dinner,

163
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:00,700
I don't even remember.

164
00:09:02,180 --> 00:09:03,060
It doesn't matter.

165
00:09:03,180 --> 00:09:04,820
But if she misunderstood,

166
00:09:05,540 --> 00:09:06,940
that's on her.

167
00:09:08,420 --> 00:09:09,860
Honey, how about this?

168
00:09:10,100 --> 00:09:10,940
I'll talk to the people

169
00:09:11,100 --> 00:09:12,500
at Ruixin Investment Bank

170
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:13,980
and ask them to switch out the manager

171
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:15,180
for a guy.

172
00:09:16,060 --> 00:09:17,460
That should put your mind at ease, right?

173
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:27,140
Honey,

174
00:09:28,580 --> 00:09:29,820
why don't you trust me?

175
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:33,060
You're judging me

176
00:09:33,460 --> 00:09:35,260
because of something

177
00:09:35,940 --> 00:09:37,700
an outsider said.

178
00:09:38,940 --> 00:09:40,780
Are you really not believing me?

179
00:09:43,340 --> 00:09:44,180
Honey,

180
00:09:46,380 --> 00:09:47,900
when did you

181
00:09:48,980 --> 00:09:50,220
stop trusting me?

182
00:09:53,700 --> 00:09:55,460
Since you started hiding things from me.

183
00:10:19,460 --> 00:10:20,300
Honey,

184
00:10:21,820 --> 00:10:23,060
I'm going to sleep with Hu Ziyuan.

185
00:10:25,140 --> 00:10:26,700
What are you doing?

186
00:10:26,700 --> 00:10:28,540
Stop overthinking it, okay?

187
00:10:28,780 --> 00:10:30,300
I'm your husband, your family,

188
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:31,660
the closest person to you.

189
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,820
How could I hurt you?

190
00:10:35,460 --> 00:10:38,140
Sometimes men have to socialize,

191
00:10:38,260 --> 00:10:39,700
that's unavoidable.

192
00:10:41,180 --> 00:10:43,020
And you're so righteous about it.

193
00:11:00,820 --> 00:11:01,900
I'm downstairs.

194
00:11:35,140 --> 00:11:36,380
Why did you go find her?

195
00:11:37,220 --> 00:11:38,100
What do you want?

196
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:43,600
Forget it.

197
00:11:45,670 --> 00:11:46,780
No point in arguing.

198
00:11:47,060 --> 00:11:49,270
We should focus on solving the problem now.

199
00:11:50,140 --> 00:11:51,140
What kind of problem?

200
00:11:54,540 --> 00:11:56,260
She hasn't gotten any solid proof yet.

201
00:11:57,580 --> 00:11:58,660
As long as I don't admit it,

202
00:11:59,140 --> 00:12:00,420
she can't do anything.

203
00:12:03,140 --> 00:12:04,300
So you're always going to

204
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:05,260
keep me hidden, right?

205
00:12:07,140 --> 00:12:08,260
Do you have any friends

206
00:12:08,380 --> 00:12:09,860
in Ruixin Investment Bank

207
00:12:10,220 --> 00:12:11,180
who could help me out?

208
00:12:11,420 --> 00:12:12,540
Preferably a male.

209
00:12:21,140 --> 00:12:22,980
You'll have to lay low for a while.

210
00:12:23,460 --> 00:12:24,820
Once she gets past this,

211
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:26,340
I'll come back to you.

212
00:12:28,700 --> 00:12:29,540
Don't worry,

213
00:12:29,740 --> 00:12:31,820
I won't treat you badly at work.

214
00:12:31,820 --> 00:12:33,820
Please find a new male manager.

215
00:12:36,580 --> 00:12:37,460
Hu Cheng,

216
00:12:37,660 --> 00:12:38,860
she already knows.

217
00:12:38,980 --> 00:12:40,060
Yeah, she does.

218
00:12:40,060 --> 00:12:41,780
So we should figure out a solution.

219
00:12:41,780 --> 00:12:42,860
To solve what?

220
00:12:42,980 --> 00:12:44,260
Go back to the way things were?

221
00:12:49,300 --> 00:12:51,860
What's your purpose inviting her
to dinner today?

222
00:12:53,380 --> 00:12:55,100
Just because I didn't go
to see your grandmother?

223
00:13:02,540 --> 00:13:03,380
Qiuzi,

224
00:13:04,340 --> 00:13:05,540
I've always thought

225
00:13:06,060 --> 00:13:07,940
you were a strong person inside.

226
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:12,180
I always thought you were so open about it

227
00:13:12,180 --> 00:13:13,580
because you're not afraid of your wife.

228
00:13:22,820 --> 00:13:24,540
If you came here to argue,

229
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:26,460
then let's not talk anymore.

230
00:14:13,780 --> 00:14:15,380
I know you're feeling bad,

231
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:18,260
but my pressure is even greater than yours.

232
00:14:21,630 --> 00:14:22,600
You know,

233
00:14:24,040 --> 00:14:25,620
after all, the path we've chosen

234
00:14:26,180 --> 00:14:28,180
is much harder than most people's.

235
00:14:35,270 --> 00:14:37,180
Let's stop hurting each other, alright?

236
00:14:43,020 --> 00:14:44,180
It's getting late now.

237
00:14:45,580 --> 00:14:46,420
Why don't you

238
00:14:47,100 --> 00:14:48,260
head back now?

239
00:14:49,020 --> 00:14:49,860
I'll meet you,

240
00:14:51,670 --> 00:14:53,300
tomorrow, or this weekend.

241
00:14:54,540 --> 00:14:55,820
We can talk these through.

242
00:14:55,980 --> 00:14:56,940
You can't leave her, right?

243
00:15:06,780 --> 00:15:08,380
Is that even a question?

244
00:15:09,780 --> 00:15:10,620
I think

245
00:15:11,340 --> 00:15:13,420
we reached an agreement a long time ago.

246
00:15:13,620 --> 00:15:14,940
I didn't ask you before

247
00:15:14,940 --> 00:15:17,060
because I thought you didn't care.

248
00:15:17,900 --> 00:15:18,860
I thought your wife

249
00:15:18,860 --> 00:15:20,060
is not important in your family,

250
00:15:20,060 --> 00:15:21,860
who you'd never really care about.

251
00:15:28,700 --> 00:15:30,780
So, you do care, right?

252
00:15:31,880 --> 00:15:33,140
Like just now,

253
00:15:33,770 --> 00:15:35,620
you were still protecting her.

254
00:15:36,580 --> 00:15:38,380
When she's around, I'm nothing.

255
00:15:38,380 --> 00:15:39,900
Or what. What else can I do?

256
00:15:39,900 --> 00:15:41,660
What should I do back then?

257
00:15:42,620 --> 00:15:43,540
If you didn't bring her,

258
00:15:43,540 --> 00:15:44,740
nothing would've happened.

259
00:15:49,820 --> 00:15:51,140
When you're weak

260
00:15:51,590 --> 00:15:52,460
and indecisive,

261
00:15:52,460 --> 00:15:53,580
you come to me.

262
00:15:54,340 --> 00:15:55,460
I'm happy about that.

263
00:15:56,740 --> 00:15:58,900
I always thought you were mine.

264
00:16:00,380 --> 00:16:01,380
But in reality,

265
00:16:04,010 --> 00:16:06,500
I am no match for her, aren't I?

266
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:13,060
I can share in your misfortunes,

267
00:16:13,940 --> 00:16:14,780
but I'll never

268
00:16:14,780 --> 00:16:16,540
be the clown that highlights your happiness.

269
00:16:20,340 --> 00:16:21,740
What exactly do you want to say?

270
00:16:22,620 --> 00:16:23,900
I'm not afraid of fighting,

271
00:16:24,300 --> 00:16:25,140
of competing.

272
00:16:25,340 --> 00:16:27,580
No matter how embarrassing the process is,
I don't care.

273
00:16:29,020 --> 00:16:30,220
But in the end,

274
00:16:31,060 --> 00:16:32,220
I want to have you all to myself.

275
00:16:46,930 --> 00:16:48,380
Let me ask you one more time.

276
00:16:50,250 --> 00:16:51,620
Have you ever considered

277
00:16:51,620 --> 00:16:52,500
leaving her?

278
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:56,260
Are you threatening me?

279
00:17:01,340 --> 00:17:02,860
Do you remember

280
00:17:04,180 --> 00:17:05,100
what I said

281
00:17:05,100 --> 00:17:06,660
the last time we argued?

282
00:17:08,540 --> 00:17:10,420
Don't say things

283
00:17:11,140 --> 00:17:13,100
you'll regret.

284
00:17:14,740 --> 00:17:15,860
I won't regret it.

285
00:17:29,100 --> 00:17:30,460
I hate

286
00:17:31,860 --> 00:17:33,180
being threatened by others.

287
00:17:33,340 --> 00:17:34,540
This isn't a threat.

288
00:17:37,420 --> 00:17:38,740
I used to think

289
00:17:40,940 --> 00:17:42,980
we could understand each other.

290
00:17:44,100 --> 00:17:45,220
I used to think

291
00:17:45,220 --> 00:17:47,140
you'd always stand in my shoes.

292
00:17:47,140 --> 00:17:49,660
And I knew you'd never betray me.

293
00:18:06,420 --> 00:18:07,260
Manager Tian,

294
00:18:09,380 --> 00:18:11,220
I think this is very unprofessional of you.

295
